1
00:00:51,051 --> 00:00:53,971
ALL CHARACTERS, INCIDENTS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND BACKGROUND ARE FICTITIOUS

2
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:58,225
-Here.
-Come here.

3
00:00:59,643 --> 00:01:03,855
-Come on.
-Try some of this.

4
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:42,436
This time,

5
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:45,063
it's not just a candle but a scented one.

6
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:47,482
Right?

7
00:01:48,609 --> 00:01:49,610
Yes.

8
00:02:18,639 --> 00:02:20,641
It looks like you just got stood up.

9
00:02:22,976 --> 00:02:24,895
Thank you for the ride.

10
00:02:25,145 --> 00:02:25,979
Bye then.

11
00:02:26,063 --> 00:02:26,980
Okay.

12
00:02:27,064 --> 00:02:28,065
Take care.

13
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:29,775
I'll see you around if fate allows.

14
00:02:39,242 --> 00:02:42,329
How could you be standing right there

15
00:02:43,038 --> 00:02:44,456
right then

16
00:02:45,499 --> 00:02:47,501
with a candle?

17
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:50,045
You really made my heart flutter.

18
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:54,841
You have done it, haven't you?
I'm sure you have.

19
00:02:55,509 --> 00:02:57,010
That skill was really something.

20
00:02:58,261 --> 00:02:59,638
You know,

21
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:03,642
we call that pickup skills.

22
00:03:08,146 --> 00:03:09,022
What is it?

23
00:03:09,940 --> 00:03:11,817
<i>Heart means love.</i>

24
00:03:12,359 --> 00:03:13,527
<i>In South Korea,</i>

25
00:03:14,569 --> 00:03:16,363
this means that they like you.

26
00:03:17,656 --> 00:03:19,408
I doubt that's the case, but...

27
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:20,867
What is it?

28
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:23,412
Since you said your heart fluttered...

29
00:03:29,126 --> 00:03:31,753
Just to make sure there's no confusion,

30
00:03:31,962 --> 00:03:34,965
-there's something I need to tell you.
-What's so complicated?

31
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:37,759
-What is it? Just tell me.
-I have a woman in my life.

32
00:03:39,469 --> 00:03:40,679
What?

33
00:03:41,763 --> 00:03:43,056
She's my fiancée.

34
00:03:44,433 --> 00:03:45,267
Hold on.

35
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:49,438
What did you just say?

36
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:51,940
-I have a fiancée--
-No, before that.

37
00:03:52,023 --> 00:03:54,234
-I have a woman--
-No, even before that.

38
00:03:55,569 --> 00:03:58,697
Just to prevent
any fluster you might go through...

39
00:03:58,780 --> 00:03:59,948
Yes, that one.

40
00:04:00,407 --> 00:04:02,576
That sounds very offending.

41
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:04,494
Flustered? Who?

42
00:04:04,745 --> 00:04:05,871
Me? Why?

43
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:07,789
I'm not confused at all.

44
00:04:07,873 --> 00:04:09,708
There seems to be a misunderstanding here.

45
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:12,043
Whether you have a woman or not,

46
00:04:13,462 --> 00:04:17,340
I don't care at all.
Do you understand? I have a man too.

47
00:04:17,424 --> 00:04:19,301
I have many men in Seoul.

48
00:04:20,469 --> 00:04:22,387
-Many?
-Yes.

49
00:04:22,554 --> 00:04:25,056
I'm sure they are
all crying their eyes out now.

50
00:04:25,140 --> 00:04:26,975
Which is why I need to hurry back.

51
00:04:27,058 --> 00:04:29,060
Are you saying you're going back for men?

52
00:04:29,728 --> 00:04:31,688
Partly because of men.

53
00:04:32,314 --> 00:04:33,940
I have to go back anyway.

54
00:04:34,858 --> 00:04:36,610
It's not like I will live here.

55
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:38,612
That's not what I meant to say.

56
00:04:38,862 --> 00:04:40,739
Even if you tell me to stay, I won't.

57
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:43,617
Anyway, this is really offending.

58
00:04:44,117 --> 00:04:46,495
You just drew the line, Mr. Ri.

59
00:04:46,745 --> 00:04:48,246
Because you don't want me to cross it.

60
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:52,250
That's a nice way to put it.

61
00:04:54,377 --> 00:04:57,631
Don't worry.
I'm very good at not crossing lines.

62
00:04:57,714 --> 00:05:00,217
I have never even been fined
while driving.

63
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,426
I never cross lines.

64
00:05:01,510 --> 00:05:03,512
I keep my eyes to the front
and never look sideways.

65
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:07,599
Don't you have to look sideways a little
when you drive?

66
00:05:08,892 --> 00:05:11,061
Is that important now?
Don't you get the point?

67
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:21,363
Are you an actor?
How are you so good at our dialect?

68
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:23,156
There's nothing a con man can't do.

69
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:25,075
I can even speak Jeju dialect.

70
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:40,048
-Could you stop the car for a while?
-Pardon?

71
00:05:40,131 --> 00:05:41,675
Stop the car!

72
00:05:47,764 --> 00:05:50,016
-What's the matter?
-I thought I saw someone I knew.

73
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:52,310
I don't think you know anyone here.

74
00:05:52,602 --> 00:05:54,563
-I guess you're right.
-Hurry up and get in.

75
00:05:56,273 --> 00:05:57,691
She looked just like her.

76
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:03,405
Excuse me.

77
00:06:04,906 --> 00:06:05,824
What brings you here?

78
00:06:07,576 --> 00:06:08,994
Who are you looking for?

79
00:06:09,536 --> 00:06:11,288
I'm here to see Ri Jeong Hyeok.

80
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:13,164
At this time?

81
00:06:13,748 --> 00:06:15,959
How do you know Jeong Hyeok?

82
00:06:16,543 --> 00:06:18,003
Why do I have to answer that?

83
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:24,259
I'm the head of this village.

84
00:06:24,843 --> 00:06:26,845
Let me see your pass.

85
00:06:32,142 --> 00:06:33,351
SEO DAN

86
00:06:38,023 --> 00:06:41,902
So you still don't want to tell us
what your relationship with him is?

87
00:06:41,985 --> 00:06:43,278
I'm his fiancée.

88
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:47,949
What did you just say?

89
00:06:48,033 --> 00:06:50,368
I'm Ri Jeong Hyeok's fiancée.

90
00:06:52,537 --> 00:06:53,496
But...

91
00:06:55,498 --> 00:06:56,750
Let's go.

92
00:07:02,088 --> 00:07:05,050
I can't believe you were two-timing.
You didn't look like you would.

93
00:07:06,927 --> 00:07:07,928
Two-timing?

94
00:07:08,219 --> 00:07:09,596
I don't think that's true.

95
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:11,723
Of course it is true.
You have two fiancées.

96
00:07:11,806 --> 00:07:13,725
This would make a headline.

97
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:15,769
You're not my fiancée.

98
00:07:16,227 --> 00:07:17,812
You said I was your fiancée.

99
00:07:17,896 --> 00:07:19,439
I didn't say it. You said it first.

100
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:20,857
Because I thought you'd be gone--

101
00:07:20,941 --> 00:07:23,526
Well, I couldn't. Okay? I couldn't.

102
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:24,903
Why do you keep saying that?

103
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:28,323
And what if this troubles us later?

104
00:07:28,740 --> 00:07:30,075
Then we will all be screwed.

105
00:07:30,659 --> 00:07:32,452
-That won't happen.
-How do you know?

106
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:34,204
What if she comes here?

107
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:35,830
Can't you do calculations?

108
00:07:35,914 --> 00:07:37,791
She's studying in Russia now.

109
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:40,543
Which means she won't be here for a while.

110
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:43,213
Do you think
I haven't thought that through?

111
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:44,714
I'm not stupid.

112
00:08:22,711 --> 00:08:24,629
The trouble happened, right?

113
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:31,511
So you were stupid, Mr. Ri.
What are you going to do now?

114
00:08:41,146 --> 00:08:42,272
It's been a while.

115
00:08:42,772 --> 00:08:44,357
When did you come from Russia?

116
00:08:44,441 --> 00:08:45,942
It's been a few days.

117
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:48,028
I'm sorry I haven't given you a heads-up.

118
00:08:48,611 --> 00:08:51,781
I heard my uncle lent you a car.
I came to pick it up.

119
00:08:53,283 --> 00:08:55,660
I was going to bring it back this weekend.

120
00:08:55,744 --> 00:08:56,661
I see.

121
00:08:59,789 --> 00:09:03,626
-This woman is--
-My mom wonders how you're doing.

122
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:05,462
Come visit Pyongyang one of those days.

123
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:07,422
Let's have dinner with our parents.

124
00:09:08,631 --> 00:09:11,468
Give me the car key. I'll get going.

125
00:09:12,719 --> 00:09:14,679
It's dangerous to drive alone
at this hour.

126
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:17,474
The roads here are rough unlike
in Pyongyang.

127
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:19,392
Then what should I do?

128
00:09:19,976 --> 00:09:21,603
Let me ride you home.

129
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:24,272
Thank you.

130
00:09:25,023 --> 00:09:28,860
And this woman is carrying out
a mission with me.

131
00:09:29,652 --> 00:09:30,487
She's my colleague.

132
00:09:33,656 --> 00:09:34,657
Is that so?

133
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:38,078
Yes, I guess it is.

134
00:09:38,161 --> 00:09:40,497
What happens when you achieve your goal?

135
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:42,332
Will you be still seeing each other then?

136
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:43,875
We won't see each other again then.

137
00:09:49,005 --> 00:09:50,131
He's right.

138
00:09:50,924 --> 00:09:52,467
Our relationship is

139
00:09:53,218 --> 00:09:55,428
sort of a strategic alliance.

140
00:09:55,512 --> 00:09:58,807
So once we complete the mission,
we won't see each other.

141
00:09:58,890 --> 00:10:00,350
Never in our lives, ever.

142
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:02,852
So please don't misunderstand.

143
00:10:02,936 --> 00:10:04,479
And my accent is a bit weird, right?

144
00:10:04,562 --> 00:10:06,731
I belong to Division 11.

145
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:11,277
There's a special and sad story
behind this. That's all I can say.

146
00:10:12,362 --> 00:10:13,613
I don't care.

147
00:10:15,865 --> 00:10:19,369
At least there's no misunderstanding then.
I'm glad.

148
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:30,213
I guess I should go home now.

149
00:10:30,296 --> 00:10:32,632
Give a safe ride to your fiancée.

150
00:10:34,926 --> 00:10:35,885
What is it?

151
00:10:42,934 --> 00:10:44,394
It's not like your home is elsewhere.

152
00:10:44,936 --> 00:10:48,231
It's dark outside,
so lock the door and stay inside.

153
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:51,401
I'll be right back.

154
00:10:58,408 --> 00:10:59,701
Let's go.

155
00:11:43,411 --> 00:11:45,914
Do you know how many times we have met?

156
00:11:50,210 --> 00:11:51,794
This is the seventh time.

157
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:54,797
We met together
with our parents four times,

158
00:11:56,007 --> 00:11:58,426
and the fifth time we met, we got engaged.

159
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:00,470
And that's seven years ago.

160
00:12:01,512 --> 00:12:02,722
Has it been that long already?

161
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:05,099
Marriage comes after engagement.

162
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:07,644
That's the right order.

163
00:12:08,645 --> 00:12:11,064
But don't you feel like
there's something missing?

164
00:12:14,442 --> 00:12:15,568
Love

165
00:12:16,486 --> 00:12:17,779
is missing.

166
00:12:19,989 --> 00:12:21,241
We should love too.

167
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:23,451
We're going to get married.

168
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:26,913
I will do everything in order.

169
00:12:28,289 --> 00:12:29,332
Please cooperate.

170
00:12:30,333 --> 00:12:31,251
I will try.

171
00:12:35,255 --> 00:12:36,297
Right.

172
00:12:36,798 --> 00:12:39,467
I'll call my mother
and tell her we're coming together.

173
00:12:43,221 --> 00:12:44,722
<i>At nine in the morning...</i>

174
00:12:50,228 --> 00:12:51,062
What do you think?

175
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:52,772
Well...

176
00:12:56,693 --> 00:12:57,694
Goodness.

177
00:12:57,777 --> 00:13:00,697
-Does it stand out too much?
-Well, yes.

178
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:06,244
-What about this?
-You're not the one getting married.

179
00:13:06,327 --> 00:13:08,663
Show some interest, will you?

180
00:13:08,746 --> 00:13:11,165
I'm meeting my son-in-law
finally after years.

181
00:13:11,249 --> 00:13:13,960
Technically, he's not your son-in-law yet.

182
00:13:16,713 --> 00:13:18,673
Just being polite should be enough.

183
00:13:18,756 --> 00:13:20,049
"Polite"?

184
00:13:29,309 --> 00:13:30,727
Tie up your hair at least.

185
00:13:30,810 --> 00:13:33,521
He might think you're a ghost
and pass out.

186
00:13:34,022 --> 00:13:37,608
Shut up and go wait outside.

187
00:13:37,692 --> 00:13:38,860
Why?

188
00:13:39,319 --> 00:13:42,572
What if Jeong Hyeok leaves
right after he takes the car back?

189
00:13:43,156 --> 00:13:45,867
Make sure you bring him here
to our house, okay?

190
00:14:03,343 --> 00:14:04,385
Jeong Hyeok!

191
00:14:04,469 --> 00:14:09,098
Since you came all the way here,
at least say hello to our family.

192
00:14:21,235 --> 00:14:22,487
Welcome.

193
00:14:28,743 --> 00:14:30,036
MAKE PYONGYANG THE MODEL CITY

194
00:14:30,119 --> 00:14:31,329
Comrade Operator.

195
00:14:31,412 --> 00:14:32,622
I appreciate your work.

196
00:14:33,164 --> 00:14:34,957
We are going to the 13th floor.

197
00:14:36,751 --> 00:14:39,003
You're headed to
the department store owner's place.

198
00:14:39,629 --> 00:14:42,423
Are you going to stay overnight?
Then I need to make a report.

199
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:44,592
No, I'm just dropping by.

200
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:55,770
You haven't met for years. I'm sure
you're glad to see each other again.

201
00:14:56,354 --> 00:15:00,525
No wonder why Jeong Hyeok drove you
all the way here.

202
00:15:00,608 --> 00:15:03,319
Dan, Jeong Hyeok may look cold,

203
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:06,614
but he's sincerer than any other man.

204
00:15:06,697 --> 00:15:07,907
He's different from other men.

205
00:15:07,990 --> 00:15:11,119
You haven't met for over seven years.
Other men would have cheated already,

206
00:15:11,202 --> 00:15:12,578
two-timing, three-timing.

207
00:15:12,662 --> 00:15:16,374
Some assholes would have even taken
a woman home and lived with her.

208
00:15:16,457 --> 00:15:17,917
-Uncle.
-What is it?

209
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,669
-Let's be quiet.
-Okay.

210
00:15:29,095 --> 00:15:31,889
Myeong Eun, you're only wearing socks.

211
00:15:31,973 --> 00:15:33,641
Hey, you came.

212
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:35,893
It's been a while.
I'm sorry for coming this late.

213
00:15:35,977 --> 00:15:38,729
Don't say that. It's not late at all.

214
00:15:39,313 --> 00:15:40,481
What's late is your marriage.

215
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:44,735
-Come on in and have dinner with us.
-I'm good, thanks.

216
00:15:44,819 --> 00:15:45,903
I already prepared it.

217
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:48,197
I already made dinner.

218
00:15:49,115 --> 00:15:51,200
We usually have dinner at this hour.

219
00:15:51,284 --> 00:15:52,702
It's okay. Come on in.

220
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:56,164
-But I had dinner already.
-Haven't you gone home yet?

221
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:59,292
-Come on. This way.
-Thanks.

222
00:16:08,342 --> 00:16:11,846
This is how we would normally eat.

223
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:13,347
Thank you.

224
00:16:13,431 --> 00:16:15,850
Make yourself comfortable
and help yourself.

225
00:16:16,434 --> 00:16:18,186
-Thanks.
-Eat up.

226
00:16:21,022 --> 00:16:25,776
All the matchmakers somehow figured out
that Dan came back from Russia

227
00:16:26,486 --> 00:16:28,863
and begged me that
they would like to see her just once.

228
00:16:28,946 --> 00:16:32,992
I told her she's already engaged,
but they were so persistent.

229
00:16:33,451 --> 00:16:36,245
They're really bugging me these days.
I'm very tired.

230
00:16:36,329 --> 00:16:37,955
Persistent? Who is?

231
00:16:42,043 --> 00:16:45,213
I mean, I just have never
heard about this.

232
00:16:48,257 --> 00:16:49,342
Open your mouth.

233
00:16:50,927 --> 00:16:53,387
Chew on this and keep your mouth shut.

234
00:16:57,642 --> 00:17:00,311
Eat up. It's well-grilled.

235
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:14,700
Could it be her doppelgänger?

236
00:17:15,284 --> 00:17:16,452
She looked just like her.

237
00:17:31,217 --> 00:17:34,053
-Are you finished already?
-Didn't my brother say

238
00:17:34,929 --> 00:17:37,265
that my nickname was Picky Princess?

239
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:42,061
Unless the food is really good,
I can't have more than three bites.

240
00:17:44,855 --> 00:17:46,190
The chef here is pretty good too,

241
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:48,234
but I'll take you
to a better place next time.

242
00:17:49,443 --> 00:17:52,572
You don't have to.
There won't be next time.

243
00:17:54,115 --> 00:17:56,534
Your brother didn't tell me this,

244
00:17:57,118 --> 00:17:59,954
so I didn't know you'd be this pretty.
I wish there is next time.

245
00:18:00,746 --> 00:18:02,456
I heard
you had a perfect academic background

246
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:04,917
and had a good eye for your age.

247
00:18:05,001 --> 00:18:08,004
I heard you make clever investments.

248
00:18:09,255 --> 00:18:13,634
My second brother seemed
to have fallen in love with you.

249
00:18:13,718 --> 00:18:16,220
-You're flattering me.
-But Mr. Gu,

250
00:18:17,013 --> 00:18:18,389
I won't fall for you.

251
00:18:19,348 --> 00:18:20,808
I can see everything.

252
00:18:20,891 --> 00:18:22,977
You're just laying the groundwork now

253
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:25,021
for a bigger purpose.

254
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:28,399
It looks like you want to marry me
so you can have it all.

255
00:18:29,859 --> 00:18:31,193
And I don't think it will happen.

256
00:18:32,778 --> 00:18:34,864
I grew up in a tough family,

257
00:18:34,947 --> 00:18:36,699
so I have very sharp eyes.

258
00:18:36,782 --> 00:18:40,161
Take some pocket money
from my brother and wrap it up.

259
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:46,626
Even the wine is lame.

