01:02:30,288 --> 01:02:31,581
-Buy skewered meat!
-Here.

1026
01:02:31,665 --> 01:02:35,752
<i>Buy firewood! Buy firewood!</i>

1027
01:02:35,835 --> 01:02:39,214
-Buy chicken!
-I have blankets!

1028
01:02:39,881 --> 01:02:41,591
-Buy chicken! Buy chicken!
-Buy firewood!

1029
01:02:43,677 --> 01:02:45,303
Buy corn cake!

1030
01:02:45,387 --> 01:02:47,347
Buy corn cake!

1031
01:02:51,768 --> 01:02:55,105
Are you saying we need to sleep outside

1032
01:02:55,230 --> 01:02:57,315
on a bed of corn leaves?

1033
01:02:57,399 --> 01:03:00,402
It's cold inside and outside the train.

1034
01:03:01,069 --> 01:03:02,654
At least you can build a fire outside.

1035
01:03:03,530 --> 01:03:06,241
Still, this is too...

1036
01:03:08,535 --> 01:03:10,328
I think it would be warmer
inside the train.

1037
01:03:19,337 --> 01:03:20,422
Buy firewood!

1038
01:03:20,505 --> 01:03:23,842
Buy firewood! We got firewood!

1039
01:03:23,925 --> 01:03:25,135
Buy firewood!

1040
01:03:26,052 --> 01:03:27,929
Buy firewood!

1041
01:03:28,179 --> 01:03:29,848
Buy firewood!

1042
01:03:30,557 --> 01:03:33,518
Buy firewood! Buy firewood!

1043
01:03:36,563 --> 01:03:37,689
My goodness.

1044
01:03:40,442 --> 01:03:41,901
Buy firewood!

1045
01:03:42,235 --> 01:03:43,570
It's warm.

1046
01:03:45,488 --> 01:03:46,573
Those people have blankets.

1047
01:03:47,365 --> 01:03:48,450
Did they buy them?

1048
01:03:48,825 --> 01:03:49,951
Did they bring them?

1049
01:04:00,962 --> 01:04:02,547
It's nice and warm.

1050
01:04:02,839 --> 01:04:04,507
I can stretch my legs, too.

1051
01:04:04,591 --> 01:04:07,969
I feel like I got an upgrade
from economy class to business class.

1052
01:04:08,053 --> 01:04:09,846
I am glad I came outside.

1053
01:04:11,890 --> 01:04:13,641
Mr. Ri, sit down. It's warm.

1054
01:04:18,605 --> 01:04:19,773
Corns and potatoes!

1055
01:04:24,194 --> 01:04:25,528
Where are you going?

1056
01:04:36,706 --> 01:04:37,999
It looks delicious!

1057
01:04:38,541 --> 01:04:39,751
Mr. Ri, you should eat.

1058
01:04:40,835 --> 01:04:42,212
You said you weren't hungry.

1059
01:04:42,921 --> 01:04:44,130
It's so delicious!

1060
01:04:49,761 --> 01:04:51,012
By the way, Mr. Ri.

1061
01:04:51,262 --> 01:04:52,097
I saw

1062
01:04:52,764 --> 01:04:55,392
people over there
buy water to wash their faces.

1063
01:04:55,475 --> 01:04:57,352
50 won for cold water
and 100 won for hot water.

1064
01:04:57,435 --> 01:05:00,313
Although hot water costs twice as much,
it would be better, right?

1065
01:05:00,397 --> 01:05:02,732
Are you thinking about settling down here?

1066
01:05:02,899 --> 01:05:04,150
Do you want to live here?

1067
01:05:04,567 --> 01:05:07,070
How could one be so greedy?

1068
01:05:10,281 --> 01:05:11,533
Unbelievable.

1069
01:05:11,616 --> 01:05:13,868
Don't act like
I am the greediest person on earth

1070
01:05:14,160 --> 01:05:16,663
just because I wanted the 100-won water
to wash my face!

1071
01:05:19,791 --> 01:05:21,000
I have money, okay?

1072
01:05:21,543 --> 01:05:23,294
I will pay for my own water.

1073
01:05:23,378 --> 01:05:24,712
Where did you get that money?

1074
01:05:26,506 --> 01:05:28,216
I pawned my watch.

1075
01:05:29,008 --> 01:05:31,719
They weighed my designer watch.

1076
01:05:32,387 --> 01:05:36,224
Buying all the clothes I wanted
left me with 500 won.

1077
01:05:38,393 --> 01:05:40,812
There was a really nice men's watch
at the pawnshop.

1078
01:05:40,979 --> 01:05:42,313
Are you listening to me?

1079
01:05:44,774 --> 01:05:47,485
People here don't listen to me.
They don't even try.

1080
01:05:48,111 --> 01:05:49,529
Gosh, it's hot!

1081
01:05:50,905 --> 01:05:51,990
It's so hot.

1082
01:06:04,252 --> 01:06:06,296
Mr. Ri, you are a good man.

1083
01:06:06,838 --> 01:06:07,839
That was sudden.

1084
01:06:08,256 --> 01:06:11,259
Well, I suddenly had that thought.

1085
01:06:11,843 --> 01:06:12,844
Later on,

1086
01:06:13,595 --> 01:06:17,515
you will be a good husband and a good dad.

1087
01:06:18,016 --> 01:06:19,309
I don't know.

1088
01:06:20,393 --> 01:06:22,604
I haven't thought about the future.

1089
01:06:23,563 --> 01:06:24,397
Why not?

1090
01:06:29,444 --> 01:06:31,696
When things don't go as I thought,

1091
01:06:32,238 --> 01:06:33,823
I get disappointed.

1092
01:06:35,700 --> 01:06:37,243
Has that happened to you?

1093
01:06:56,596 --> 01:06:57,889
Yes.

1094
01:07:02,435 --> 01:07:05,772
I can see it broke your heart.

1095
01:07:17,242 --> 01:07:19,118
There is an Indian proverb that goes,

1096
01:07:19,786 --> 01:07:23,456
"Sometimes, the wrong train takes you
to the right station."

1097
01:07:25,708 --> 01:07:27,126
It was like that for me, too.

1098
01:07:27,710 --> 01:07:29,128
Throughout my life,

1099
01:07:30,922 --> 01:07:33,007
I always felt like
I was on the wrong train.

1100
01:07:33,091 --> 01:07:34,926
One time,

1101
01:07:35,385 --> 01:07:36,970
I wanted to give up.

1102
01:07:37,470 --> 01:07:39,556
I didn't want to go anywhere.

1103
01:07:42,684 --> 01:07:44,602
So I thought about jumping off the train.

1104
01:07:48,314 --> 01:07:50,108
Look where I am now.

1105
01:07:52,193 --> 01:07:55,363
I took the wrong train again,
and a very wrong one at that.

1106
01:07:55,446 --> 01:07:57,949
It even got me across the 38th parallel!

1107
01:08:08,626 --> 01:08:09,919
Still,

1108
01:08:12,046 --> 01:08:14,382
you should think about the future

1109
01:08:15,174 --> 01:08:16,968
even if things don't always go
as you wish.

1110
01:08:18,386 --> 01:08:19,637
I wish

1111
01:08:21,139 --> 01:08:22,974
you could be happy

1112
01:08:24,350 --> 01:08:26,728
even after I leave, Jeong Hyeok.

1113
01:08:29,147 --> 01:08:31,232
I want you to arrive at the right station

1114
01:08:32,483 --> 01:08:34,986
no matter which train you take.

1115
01:08:42,744 --> 01:08:44,245
This is so romantic.

1116
01:08:45,079 --> 01:08:46,623
So romantic I could die.

1117
01:08:49,709 --> 01:08:51,878
Wake up!

1118
01:08:53,963 --> 01:08:56,382
If you are tired, lean on me.

1119
01:08:56,466 --> 01:08:57,425
Gosh!

1120
01:08:57,759 --> 01:08:58,926
Are you crazy?

1121
01:09:02,555 --> 01:09:05,016
I can't believe
it's colder inside the train.

1122
01:09:11,814 --> 01:09:14,192
What is your problem?

1123
01:09:14,275 --> 01:09:15,526
For goodness' sake.

1124
01:09:17,695 --> 01:09:19,947
How am I supposed to live this way
for ten years?

1125
01:11:06,095 --> 01:11:09,515
LET US PRODUCE MORE MEAT AND MILK

1126
01:11:20,651 --> 01:11:23,863
-Hurry on out.
-Let's move.

1127
01:11:34,749 --> 01:11:36,876
This place is completely different!

1128
01:11:37,710 --> 01:11:40,546
-Really?
-Hurry up and come here.

1129
01:11:40,630 --> 01:11:43,090
Stop looking wildly around.
You look like a country bumpkin.

1130
01:11:43,883 --> 01:11:46,511
Hold on. What did you call me?
A country bumpkin?

1131
01:11:47,595 --> 01:11:51,265
I am the exact opposite
of a country bumpkin, okay?

1132
01:11:51,349 --> 01:11:53,601
You aren't listening to me again.
Wait for me.

1133
01:12:00,691 --> 01:12:02,193
A two-hour car ride

1134
01:12:02,276 --> 01:12:04,445
turned into a 17-hour train ride!

1135
01:12:04,529 --> 01:12:06,364
It happens here sometimes.

1136
01:12:06,447 --> 01:12:08,616
It shouldn't happen!

1137
01:12:09,283 --> 01:12:12,036
Are you not going back?
Why do you have so much luggage?

1138
01:12:12,537 --> 01:12:15,039
I packed this and that.

1139
01:12:15,540 --> 01:12:16,791
All right.

1140
01:12:26,008 --> 01:12:27,635
I will take the photo now.

1141
01:12:28,177 --> 01:12:31,347
Look over here. One, two, three.

1142
01:12:32,723 --> 01:12:34,016
All done.

1143
01:12:35,476 --> 01:12:38,312
Excuse me. I think I closed my eyes.

1144
01:12:38,396 --> 01:12:39,689
Should I ask for another shot?

1145
01:12:39,772 --> 01:12:40,857
It's okay.

1146
01:12:41,107 --> 01:12:43,025
This photo is for verifying your identity,

1147
01:12:43,442 --> 01:12:44,986
so you shouldn't look too pretty in it.

1148
01:12:45,570 --> 01:12:47,655
I should. How else
would they know it's me?

1149
01:12:48,489 --> 01:12:49,574
Let's go.

1150
01:12:50,283 --> 01:12:51,409
You know,

1151
01:12:52,910 --> 01:12:55,580
why don't we get our photo taken?

1152
01:12:56,163 --> 01:12:57,248
I mean,

1153
01:12:57,665 --> 01:13:00,501
we won't see each other again
after I leave.

1154
01:13:00,751 --> 01:13:01,836
It will be a memento.

1155
01:13:06,257 --> 01:13:07,967
There is no need for us to remember

1156
01:13:08,968 --> 01:13:10,344
or keep a memento of each other.

1157
01:13:12,805 --> 01:13:14,265
You have a point.

1158
01:13:15,516 --> 01:13:17,226
I was just saying.

1159
01:13:27,570 --> 01:13:28,571
Welcome.

1160
01:13:28,654 --> 01:13:30,781
I booked a room under Mr. Cheon.

1161
01:13:31,574 --> 01:13:33,034
Please wait.

1162
01:13:41,292 --> 01:13:43,920
FRONT DESK

1163
01:13:44,003 --> 01:13:45,296
The room number is 1511.

1164
01:13:46,005 --> 01:13:47,298
Let's go.

1165
01:13:54,847 --> 01:13:55,973
All right.

1166
01:13:56,515 --> 01:13:58,392
I will get washed up and change.

1167
01:13:58,476 --> 01:14:01,479
Let's eat first. I am terribly hungry.

1168
01:14:01,562 --> 01:14:02,772
Okay.

1169
01:14:19,288 --> 01:14:20,456
It's me.

1170
01:14:20,957 --> 01:14:22,625
We arrived at Pyongyang Hotel.

1171
01:14:23,876 --> 01:14:26,420
He hasn't figured anything out,
so don't worry.

1172
01:14:27,672 --> 01:14:30,967
For some reason, I can't get ahold
of Lieutenant Commander Cho.

1173
01:14:31,968 --> 01:14:33,260
By the way,

1174
01:14:34,178 --> 01:14:36,847
can we really trust him to pay a tenfold?

1175
01:14:38,766 --> 01:14:42,478
We need to get the money
before we hand him over!

1176
01:14:46,649 --> 01:14:47,858
Give me the phone.

1177
01:15:07,128 --> 01:15:10,381
Mr. Cheon, why did you hang up?

1178
01:15:10,965 --> 01:15:12,383
Manager Oh, you little...

1179
01:15:12,925 --> 01:15:16,554
How could you do this
after getting so much money from me?

1180
01:15:16,846 --> 01:15:18,389
<i>Why are you doing this?</i>

1181
01:15:19,682 --> 01:15:21,225
<i>Hello? Hey.</i>

1182
01:15:21,308 --> 01:15:23,811
Who will pay you a tenfold? Who?

1183
01:15:24,937 --> 01:15:27,898
Seung-jun, it seems like
I am a good judge of character.

1184
01:15:28,524 --> 01:15:30,943
<i>You are so intelligent.</i>

1185
01:15:31,027 --> 01:15:33,404
Who would have thought to find you there?

1186
01:15:35,156 --> 01:15:38,701
I love how you scold and praise me
in a situation like this.

1187
01:15:39,410 --> 01:15:41,704
This is why I respect you.

1188
01:15:42,288 --> 01:15:43,998
You are decisive.

1189
01:15:44,498 --> 01:15:45,458
Quit babbling.

1190
01:15:46,042 --> 01:15:48,002
Prepare to die once you get here

1191
01:15:48,294 --> 01:15:49,628
after you give me my money back.

1192
01:15:50,212 --> 01:15:51,380
You bastard.

1193
01:15:51,464 --> 01:15:52,298
<i>Mr. Yoon,</i>

1194
01:15:53,174 --> 01:15:55,259
it wasn't my intention.

1195
01:15:55,342 --> 01:15:57,094
When you run a business...

1196
01:15:58,888 --> 01:15:59,722
<i>Hello?</i>

1197
01:16:00,765 --> 01:16:01,640
<i>Hello?</i>

1198
01:16:02,058 --> 01:16:03,392
<i>Why did you stop?</i>

1199
01:16:03,976 --> 01:16:05,019
Mr. Yoon.

1200
01:16:05,102 --> 01:16:05,936
<i>What?</i>

1201
01:16:06,437 --> 01:16:08,105
How is Se-ri?

1202
01:16:08,230 --> 01:16:11,776
Why did you bring her up so suddenly?
It's a sad topic.

1203
01:16:11,859 --> 01:16:14,361
Se-ri is gone. I wish I could see her.

1204
01:16:15,571 --> 01:16:16,739
I am seeing her.

1205
01:16:17,323 --> 01:16:18,449
What did you say?

1206
01:16:18,532 --> 01:16:20,409
It's nothing.
What do you mean she is gone?

1207
01:16:20,493 --> 01:16:23,037
Must you ask? She is dead.

1208
01:16:23,621 --> 01:16:24,705
Dead?

1209
01:16:25,748 --> 01:16:26,624
Why?

1210
01:16:26,707 --> 01:16:28,584
It's none of your business.

1211
01:16:29,168 --> 01:16:32,129
I guess you will see her in heaven soon.

1212
01:16:32,713 --> 01:16:34,465
Send her my regards when you see her.

1213
01:16:35,049 --> 01:16:35,883
I will do that.

1214
01:16:36,842 --> 01:16:38,052
I will send her your regards.

1215
01:16:38,427 --> 01:16:40,054
I think I will be able to do that.

1216
01:16:44,475 --> 01:16:46,143
You really are Yoon Se-ri!

1217
01:16:46,227 --> 01:16:47,103
I mean...

1218
01:16:47,186 --> 01:16:48,312
How...

1219
01:16:50,731 --> 01:16:52,149
Where are you taking me?

1220
01:16:55,653 --> 01:16:57,363
This has to be fate.

1221
01:16:57,947 --> 01:17:01,492
-I guess I won't die after all.
-What are you...

1222
01:17:13,796 --> 01:17:14,922
Who are you?

1223
01:17:24,223 --> 01:17:25,266
Yoon Se-ri.

1224
01:17:25,850 --> 01:17:27,143
-I think--
-Let's break up.

1225
01:17:27,226 --> 01:17:28,769
I was going to say that.

1226
01:17:28,853 --> 01:17:30,271
Let me make this clear.

1227
01:17:30,354 --> 01:17:32,898
I broke up with you. I dumped you.

1228
01:17:33,482 --> 01:17:35,901
You can tell people that you dated me,

1229
01:17:35,985 --> 01:17:38,779
but don't even think about
spreading rumors

1230
01:17:39,029 --> 01:17:40,781
of how you dumped me.

1231
01:17:40,865 --> 01:17:43,033
You know how scary
rich people can be, right?

1232
01:17:43,367 --> 01:17:44,743
I could end you.

1233
01:17:44,827 --> 01:17:46,203
You are always like this.

1234
01:17:46,287 --> 01:17:48,539
You push people away before you get hurt.

1235
01:17:48,664 --> 01:17:50,708
You leave before you are in for a wait.

1236
01:17:51,125 --> 01:17:54,170
I hope you meet someone like you.

1237
01:17:54,920 --> 01:17:56,797
Someone who makes you wait endlessly.

1238
01:18:00,342 --> 01:18:01,719
That won't happen.

1239
01:18:02,386 --> 01:18:04,805
I will never make a fool out of myself

1240
01:18:04,972 --> 01:18:07,224
by waiting for someone.

1241
01:18:16,650 --> 01:18:17,943
Ri Jeong Hyeok.

1242
01:18:19,153 --> 01:18:20,946
What's taking him so long?

1243
01:18:22,865 --> 01:18:24,033
Crap.

1244
01:19:24,843 --> 01:19:27,304
You're protecting me
right now, Jeong Hyeok.

1245
01:19:27,388 --> 01:19:29,139
Not protecting,
but keeping my eyes on you.

1246
01:19:29,223 --> 01:19:32,184
I'm not a person who follows you around
to protect you.

1247
01:19:32,268 --> 01:19:34,979
Could I do well and not get caught?

1248
01:19:35,062 --> 01:19:36,021
You left your key.

1249
01:19:36,105 --> 01:19:37,773
If things like this happen twice in a row,

1250
01:19:37,856 --> 01:19:39,233
I should be upset, right?

1251
01:19:39,316 --> 01:19:41,318
Don't be so upset because of that man.

1252
01:19:41,402 --> 01:19:42,861
I didn't follow him.

1253
01:19:42,945 --> 01:19:44,154
We just came together.

1254
01:19:44,238 --> 01:19:47,574
I decided on a wedding date
with that man just a while ago.

1255
01:19:47,658 --> 01:19:50,369
Do you intend to keep
one more person other than me?

1256
01:19:50,452 --> 01:19:51,287
Who is she?

1257
01:19:51,370 --> 01:19:54,248
It's the liking part
that's giving me a headache.

1258
01:19:54,581 --> 01:19:56,583
Subtitle translation by Dong-joo Park
